


CLEARROT(1)              TIPSY COMMANDS               CLEARROT(1)



NAME
     clearrot - resets the viewing angle down the z-axis

SYNOPSIS
     clearrot

ALIASES
     crot

DESCRIPTION
     clearrot resets the viewing angle to  be  looking  down  the
     _z-axis.   To  view  the particles from the new direction the
     clearrot command must be followed by either the view command
     to  maintain  the  same  plot type or by viewall, viewarray,
     viewgas, viewmag, viewpot, viewrad, or viewstar commands.

SEE ALSO
     clearall(1), resetcolor(1), rotate(1), unloadall(1),  unmar-
     kall(1), unzoom(1)




































